A simple and efficient hash table implementation in c using separate chaining and fnv-1a hash function.

It supports static sized keys and values by default, but it can be overridden to support dynamic sized keys and values by supplying custom methods in the constructor.

The signature of the constructor is as follows:
hashmap_t* hashmap_create(
    size_t key_size,            // Size of the key in bytes
    size_t value_size,          // Size of the value in bytes
    size_t capacity,            // Initial capacity of the hash table
    float max_load_factor,      // Maximum load factor before resizing
    hash_fn_t hash,             // Hash function to use
    cmp_fn_t cmp,               // Comparison function to use
    key_copy_fn_t key_copy,     // Function to copy a key
    value_copy_fn_t value_copy, // Function to copy a value
    key_free_fn_t key_free,     // Function to free a key
    value_free_fn_t value_free); // Function to free a value

The signature of the supplied functions can be found in hashmap.h.

Fnv1a hashing function can be used directly from hash.h (fnv1a_hash).
